               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Daily Office prayers and litanies (fols. 3rb-13vb)
 II) Śǝrʿāta
                     qǝddāse "Ordinary of the Mass" (fols. 14ra-35rb)
 III) Anaphoras (fols.
                     35rb-120va)
 III-1) Anaphora of the Apostles (fols. 35rb-46rb)
 III-2)
                     Anaphora of Our Lord Jesus Christ (fols. 46va-49va)
 III-3) Anaphora of Our
                     Lady by St Cyriacus of Behnesa (fols. 49va-59va)
 III-4) Anaphora of St
                     John, son of Thunder (fols. 59va-67vb)
 III-5) Anaphora of the 318 Orthodox
                     Fathers of Nicaea (fols. 68ra-74vb)
 III-6) Anaphora of St John Chrysostom
                     (fols. 75ra-79va)
 III-7) Anaphora of St Jacob of Serug (fols.
                     79vb-85ra)
 III-8) Anaphora of St Gregory of Armenia ("Hosanna-liturgy of
                     St Gregory") (fols. 85rb-90vb)
 III-9) Anaphora of St Dioscorus of
                     Alexandria (fols.90vb-92vb)
 III-10) Anaphora of St Epiphanius of Cyprus
                     (fols. 92vb-98va)
 III-11) Anaphora of St Athanasius of Alexandria (fols.
                     98va-107va)
 III-12) Anaphora of St Cyril of Alexandria (fols.
                     107vb-113va)
 III-13) Anaphora of St Basil of Caesarea (fols.
                     113vb-120va)
 I) Daily Office prayers and litanies (fols. 120va-122vb)
                     
 Additiones 1-3.</summary>
