                     <origDate notBefore="1872" notAfter="1876">King Yoḥannǝs IV (r. 1872-89) is
                        mentioned on <locus target="#9ra">9ra</locus>, 33rb, 40va; Coptic Patriarch
                        Demetrius (in tenure 1862-70) is mentioned on <locus target="#35va">35va</locus>, 50ra, 50va; Metropolitan ʾAtnatewos (in tenure 1869-76) is
                        mentioned on <locus target="#33vb">33vb</locus>, 35va, 40rb, 50ra, 50va,
                        80ra, 98va. 
 <locus target="#123">123</locus> originates from a
                        different, older (late 15th or 16th century?) Ms.</origDate>
                  </origin>
               <provenance>wayzaro Tǝbläṣ is mentioned as the donor
                     according to Additio 3. ʾAskāla Māryām (possibly baptismal name of wayzaro Tǝbläṣ?) is mentioned in the supplication
                     formula in the heading of Text I. Many other names (e.g. Gabra Ḥǝywat, Fǝre
                     Māryām, Za-Walda Māryām) are mentioned in the supplication formulas throughout
                     the Ms. The names seem to have been added later.</provenance></history>
